author: app.com
title: Lakewood football tops Jackson Liberty, still unbeaten
text:
MORE JACKSON Sophomore quarterback Zyhier Jones was new to the world way back in 2000, the last time Lakewood won a division title.
Jones scored on a short run in the fourth quarter to wrap up Lakewood’s 20-3 victory over Jackson Liberty Friday night in a game that could prove to be a significant step in the Piners’ quest for another championship.
Lakewood (4-0, 4-0) kept pace with Point Boro atop Shore Conference Class B South and knocked Jackson Liberty from the ranks of the division’s undefeated.
And it’s all partly thanks to Jones’ determination on a fourth-and-goal sneak from the 1-yard line, when the 6-footer used all of his 170 pounds to help push Piners’ blockers into the end zone.
